Musalia Mudavadi (ANC), Kalonzo Musyoka (Wiper) and Moses Wetang'ula (Ford Kenya) met in Karen on Friday as events unfold following the unexpected handshake. President Uhuru Kenyatta and Nasa leader Raila Odinga have agreed to work together for the sake of peace and development in Kenya. The Nairobi meeting of the three Nasa principals came hours after ODM, a party led by Raila, decided to kick Wetang'ula (Bungoma) out of the Senate house leadership. The three party leaders were spotted in Karen but details of their meeting remain scanty.  Nasa principals Musalia Mudavadi (ANC), Kalonzo Musyoka (Wiper) and Moses Wetang'ula (Ford Kenya), and other politicians, during their meeting in Karen, Nairobi, March 16, 2018. /COURTESY After the move for his replacement, the Ford Kenya leader warned Raila that the Nasa "divorce will be noisy and messy" . Wetang'ula is to be replaced with his Siaya counterpart James Orengo. He said: "If anyone wants a divorce it will be noisy, messy and unhelpful, and it will have causalities. I'm not going anywhere. I was not invited to Nasa - I'm a founder." Sixteen ODM Senators signed the petition to oust Wetang'ula, Judith Pareno saying his election was a gentleman's agreement so it was not legally binding. More on this: Nasa divorce will be noisy and messy, Wetang'ula warns Raila More on this: Nasa affiliates threaten to divorce Raila's party for 'marrying' Jubilee Click here for the latest political news 